---
import { Picture } from "@astrojs/image/components";
import styles from "./your-guide.module.scss";
---

<section class={styles.guideContainer}>
	<h2 class={`text-style-headline-2 ${styles.sectionTitle}`}>
		Your guide for the trip
	</h2>
	<Picture
		class={styles.guidePicture}
		alt=""
		src={import("../../../../../public/content/data/crutchcorn.png")}
		widths={[96, 72]}
		sizes="96"
	/>
	<p class={`text-style-headline-3 ${styles.authorIntro}`}>
		Hi, I'm <span class={styles.authorName}>Corbin Crutchley</span>, the author
		of <span class={styles.seriesName}>The Framework Field Guide</span> ðŸ“’.
	</p>
	<div class={styles.guideTextContainer}>
		<p class={`text-style-button ${styles.titleText}`}>
			<span>Principal Engineer</span>
			<span class={styles.titleDivider}>Â·</span>
			<a
				class={`text-style-button ${styles.titleLink}`}
				href="https://stars.github.com/profiles/crutchcorn/">GitHub Star</a
			>
		</p>
		<p class={`text-style-body-medium ${styles.guideText}`}>
			With more than 8 years of web development experience and after getting to
			know these frameworks from the inside out, the 'Framework Field Guide'
			consists of knowledge I wish I had access to when I first started out.
			<br />
			<br />
			The series will take you through all the necessary stages, no matter your level
			of proficiency. My goal is to provide access to learning tools and support
			for everyone, so they can go and build their vision.
		</p>
	</div>
	<ul class={styles.metricsContainer} aria-label="Metrics about Corbin">
		<li class={styles.metricItem} aria-label="50 blog posts">
			<span class={`text-style-headline-4 ${styles.metricNumber}`}>50</span>
			<br />
			<span class={`text-style-body-small ${styles.metricName}`}
				>Blog posts</span
			>
		</li>

		<li class={styles.metricItem} aria-label="1,000 blog posts">
			<span class={`text-style-headline-4 ${styles.metricNumber}`}>1,000</span>
			<br />
			<span class={`text-style-body-small ${styles.metricName}`}
				>Hours streamed</span
			>
		</li>

		<li class={styles.metricItem} aria-label="10,000 GitHub contributions">
			<span class={`text-style-headline-4 ${styles.metricNumber}`}>10K</span>
			<br />
			<span class={`text-style-body-small ${styles.metricName}`}
				>GitHub contributions</span
			>
		</li>

		<li class={styles.metricItem} aria-label="120,000 blog reads">
			<span class={`text-style-headline-4 ${styles.metricNumber}`}>120K</span>
			<br />
			<span class={`text-style-body-small ${styles.metricName}`}
				>Blog reads</span
			>
		</li>

		<li class={styles.metricItem} aria-label="9,400,000 monthly NPM installs">
			<span class={`text-style-headline-4 ${styles.metricNumber}`}>9.4M</span>
			<br />
			<span class={`text-style-body-small ${styles.metricName}`}
				>Monthly NPM installs</span
			>
		</li>

		<li class={styles.metricItem} aria-label="Infinity silly jokes made">
			<span class={styles.metricNumberInfinityContainer}>
				<span class={styles.metricNumberInfinity}>âˆž</span>
			</span>
			<br />
			<span class={`text-style-body-small ${styles.metricName}`}
				>Silly jokes made</span
			>
		</li>
	</ul>
</section>
